    "body": "It's a little bit complicated ...\r\nSo the first request is always a handshake containing the information about an intent to use WebSockets.\r\nOur code uses the [_IsWebSocketRequest_ ](https://github.com/aspnet/WebSockets/blob/cff748cad3c8087649e82aa2420ad2347d40404e/src/Microsoft.AspNetCore.WebSockets/WebSocketMiddleware.cs#L64-L82)property to check if we can switch to websocket communication.\r\nThis property has to be TRUE and to get that value following conditions have to be met:\r\n- it has to be GET\r\n- IsUpgradableRequest == true (it's ok, it's true)\r\n- Following headers have to present: \r\nConnection: Upgrade\r\nUpgrade: websocket\r\n**Sec-WebSocket-Key: <16-byte nonce>** \r\nSec-WebSocket-Version: 13\r\n\r\nThe websockets protocol (https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6455) states that:\r\n_The request MUST include a header field with the name\r\n        |Sec-WebSocket-Key|.  The value of this header field MUST be a\r\n        nonce consisting of a randomly selected **16-byte** value that has\r\n        been base64-encoded (see Section 4 of [RFC4648]).  The nonce\r\n        MUST be selected randomly for each connection._\r\n\r\nThe key sent by nimbus is only 12 bytes long.\r\n\r\nThe nimbus request:\r\n_Frame 4: 215 bytes on wire (1720 bits), 215 bytes captured (1720 bits) on interface \\Device\\NPF_Loopback, id 0\r\nNull/Loopback\r\nInternet Protocol Version 4, Src: 127.0.0.1, Dst: 127.0.0.1\r\nTransmission Control Protocol, Src Port: 65032, Dst Port: 8559, Seq: 1, Ack: 1, Len: 171\r\nHypertext Transfer Protocol\r\n    GET / HTTP/1.1\\r\\n\r\n    Origin: http://localhost\\r\\n\r\n    Host: 127.0.0.1:8559\\r\\n\r\n    Connection: Upgrade\\r\\n\r\n    Upgrade: websocket\\r\\n\r\n    Sec-WebSocket-Version: 13\\r\\n\r\n    Sec-WebSocket-Key: **MDAwMDAwMDA1OWQx**\\r\\n\r\n    \\r\\n\r\n    [Full request URI: http://127.0.0.1:8559/]\r\n    [HTTP request 1/1]\r\n    [Response in frame: 6]_\r\n",
